verses.roman:
dāmodara kahe,-aiche mānera prakāra
trijagate kāhāṅ nāhi dekhi śuni āra

synonyms: dāmodara kahe—Svarūpa Dāmodara Gosvāmī said; aiche—such; mānera—of egoistic pride; prakāra—kind; tri-jagate—within the three worlds; kāhāṅ—anywhere; nāhi—not; dekhi—I see; śuni—I hear; āra—other.
translation: Svarūpa Dāmodara said, "There is no egoistic pride like this within the three worlds. At least I have neither seen nor heard of it.
